race.comment: NEZIHA (13) had been well educated before missing by a head at Geelong on debut. Maps well and is sure to have come on. She's in a top metro barn and should have these covered. BALTIC BLIZZARD (10) debuts for the Dwyer stable and has looked talented at the jumpouts. Looks ready to go and deserves respect. PIERRE LE QUILL (6) did a big job, beaten a whisker at Echuca. Draws awkwardly again but hits this at peak and is in the mix. KNUCKLEHEAD (2) resumes with John Allen engaged, and that's a lead. Hasn't done much at the jumpouts, but it wouldn't surprise if the Alexander-trained colt races well.
